Trexenta is a traditional subregion of Sardinia, Italy, located in the northern part of the province of Cagliari. It encompasses an area of c. 400 kmÂ², including 13 municipalities.


== Overview ==
The terrain is mostly hilly  in the eastern part, becoming more plain southwards. Economy is mostly based on agriculture, with the cultivation of cereals, olives and vines.
In the Middle Ages it was part of the Giudicato of Cagliari.


